{"id":1087341377,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"1 month, 1 week","timestamp":1698646628,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"20 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/1087341377/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Double a Number Represented as a Linked List","memory":"44.6 MB","code":"/**\n * Definition for singly-linked list.\n * public class ListNode {\n *     int val;\n *     ListNode next;\n *     ListNode() {}\n *     ListNode(int val) { this.val = val; }\n *     ListNode(int val, ListNode next) { this.val = val; this.next = next; }\n * }\n */\nclass Solution {\n    public ListNode doubleIt(ListNode head) {\n        Stack<ListNode> nodeStack=new Stack<>();\n        ListNode temp=head;\n        while(temp!=null) {\n            nodeStack.push(temp);\n            temp=temp.next;\n        }\n        int carry=0;\n        while(!nodeStack.empty()) {\n            ListNode node=nodeStack.pop();\n            node.val*=2;\n            node.val+=carry;\n            if(node.val/10==0) carry=0;\n            else {\n                carry=node.val/10;\n                node.val%=10;\n            }\n        }\n        if(carry>0) {\n            ListNode newNode=new ListNode(carry);\n            newNode.next=head;\n            head=newNode;\n        }\n        return head;\n    }\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"double-a-number-represented-as-a-linked-list","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
